#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: _posts/2019-06-15-panic-app-uninstall-and-repo-reset.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Panic app uninstall and repo reset"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2019-06-15-panic-app-uninstall-and-repo-reset.md
msgid "Sometimes we have things on our devices that are very sensitive, so much so that we need to completely hide or delete them in emergencies.  F-Droid already supports receiving [PanicKit](https://guardianproject.info/code/panickit) triggers to make F-Droid hide itself.  F-Droid v1.7 adds more alpha features to expand the range of options of what F-Droid can do in response to panic situations.  We think these can be very valuable for many users, but keep in mind, these features are alpha.  They are functionally complete, but they need to be widely tested before we can call them stable.  Specifically, the user experience should clearly communicate what kinds of data will be permanently deleted, and what kinds of data might still be left around afterwards."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2019-06-15-panic-app-uninstall-and-repo-reset.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p align=\"center\">\n"
"<img width=\"200\" src=\"{% asset posts/2019-06-15-panic-app-uninstall-and-repo-reset/screenshot_ripple.png %}\" />\n"
"<img width=\"200\" src=\"{% asset posts/2019-06-15-panic-app-uninstall-and-repo-reset/screenshot_fdroid_destructive0.png %}\" />\n"
"<img width=\"200\" src=\"{% asset posts/2019-06-15-panic-app-uninstall-and-repo-reset/screenshot_fdroid_destructive1.png %}\" />\n"
"</p>\n"
